---
import Site from "../layouts/Site.astro";
---
<Site
  title="Writ — Privacy"
  description="Writ stores everything locally. The site uses no analytics. The app makes no network requests except optional update checks."
  path="/privacy/"
>
  <section class="pr">
    <div class="pr-wrap">
      <header class="pr-head">
        <h1>Local only. No telemetry.</h1>
        <p class="pr-meta">Last reviewed 2026-06-24.</p>
      </header>

      <div class="pr-body">
        <p>
          Writ stores every keystroke on your disk, in a single SQLite database under your OS user data directory.
          That is the whole storage model. There is no cloud, no account, no sync server.
        </p>

        <h2>What the app does on the network</h2>
        <p>
          By default the desktop app makes one outbound request: at launch, it asks GitHub whether a newer release exists.
          That request sends only your platform and the current Writ version. You can disable it in Settings;
          when disabled, Writ makes zero network requests for the rest of the session.
        </p>
        <p>
          The preview pane runs under a fixed content-security-policy (<code>default-src 'none'</code>) in an isolated origin.
          Rendered HTML makes no network calls.
        </p>
        <p>
          Writ does not send crash reports, usage analytics, telemetry, or beacons. There is no opt-out because there is nothing to opt out of.
        </p>

        <h2>What this site does</h2>
        <p>
          This site is a static export served from GitHub Pages. It self-hosts its fonts.
          It runs no analytics scripts, sets no cookies, and does not embed third-party widgets.
        </p>

        <h2>Data export and deletion</h2>
        <p>
          Your buffers are plain rows in a local SQLite file. Copy it to back up; delete it to reset.
          The path is shown in <code>Settings &rarr; Storage</code>.
        </p>

        <h2>Source of truth</h2>
        <p>
          This page describes intent. The source of truth is the code:
          <a href="https://github.com/ibrahemid/writ" rel="noopener" target="_blank">github.com/ibrahemid/writ</a>.
          If you find a network call that contradicts the policy above, file an issue and it will be treated as a bug.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <style>
    .pr { padding: 6rem 0 8rem; }
    .pr-wrap { width: min(720px, 100% - 48px); margin: 0 auto; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 2.5rem; }
    .pr-head { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.5rem; }
    .pr-head h1 {
      font-family: var(--font-display);
      font-size: clamp(28px, 4vw, 46px);
      font-weight: 800;
      letter-spacing: -0.03em;
      color: var(--foreground);
      margin: 0;
    }
    .pr-meta {
      color: var(--subtle);
      font-family: var(--font-mono);
      font-size: 11px;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.08em;
      margin: 0;
    }
    .pr-body {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 1.25rem;
      font-size: 15px;
      line-height: 1.7;
      color: var(--foreground);
    }
    .pr-body p { color: var(--muted); margin: 0; max-width: 64ch; }
    .pr-body h2 {
      margin: 0.5rem 0 0;
      font-family: var(--font-display);
      font-size: 1.05rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: var(--foreground);
      letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    }
    .pr-body code {
      font-family: var(--font-mono);
      background: var(--elevated);
      color: var(--foreground);
      padding: 1px 6px;
      border-radius: 4px;
      font-size: 0.88em;
    }
    .pr-body a { color: var(--accent); text-decoration: underline; text-decoration-color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent) 40%, transparent); }
    .pr-body a:hover { text-decoration-color: var(--accent); }
  </style>
</Site>
